This PowerShell script automates updating tags on Azure Virtual Machines (VMs) using a CSV file as input. Hereâ€™s a breakdown of its functionality:

What the script does:
Authenticates to Azure using Connect-AzAccount.
Imports VM data from a CSV file containing columns:
"Computer Name" (VM name)
"Subscription" (Subscription ID)
"Backup Tag Name" (Tag key)
"Backup Tag Value" (Tag value)
Validates the CSV structure, ensuring all required columns exist.
Iterates through each VM entry in the CSV:
Sets the subscription context.
Retrieves the VM using Get-AzVM.
Checks if the tag is already set correctly. If so, it skips updating.
Uses Update-AzTag with the Merge operation to update tags without overwriting existing ones.
Logs successes and failures.
Displays a summary of successful and failed updates.
